Punjab (Rawalpindi). 18 Nov 2016. The dengue fever outbreak in Rawalpindi has reached a drastic level as 40 more patients were reported to have been admitted in various hospitals within last 24 hours, Dunya News reported. The toll of patients affected by the bite of _Aedes_ mosquitoes has reached a drastic figure of 3600 during this year [2016]. Moreover, 4 deaths from dengue fever have also been confirmed in Rawalpindi District.
