Sindh (Karachi). 27 Nov 2016. At least 43 more dengue fever cases surfaced in the metropolitan area within a week, taking the dengue patient toll to 1773 since 1 Jan [2016]. According to the Prevention and Control Programme for Dengue in Sindh's weekly report, at least 59 new dengue fever cases surfaced in Sindh province from 18-24 Nov 2016, out of which 43 were reported in Karachi, 11 in Mithi or Tharparkar and 5 in Hyderabad. Out of the 43 dengue fever cases, 8 were reported from District Central, 7 from District South, 6 from District West, 14 from District East, 5 from District Korangi and 3 from District Malir. A total of 3 deaths were reported from dengue fever in the province so far, out of which 2 were from Karachi and one was from Shaheed Benazirabad, while another death caused by dengue fever in the city could not be confirmed by health officials.
