Northern Hemisphere
-------------------
China
As of 31 Oct 2016, there were 1840 cases of dengue reported in China in 2016. This number is lower than that reported during the same period in 2015.

Malaysia
In week 45, the number of dengue cases was 1373, an increase from 1263 cases reported in the previous week (an increase by 8.7 percent). The cumulative number of cases in 2016 (91 879 cases) is less than that reported during the same period in 2015 (104 910 cases). As of week 45, the cumulative number of dengue deaths for 2016 was 212 cases, compared to 284 deaths during the same period in 2015.

Philippines (No update)
As of 20 Aug 2016, there were 101 401 suspected cases of dengue reported in 2016, including 422 deaths. This is 16 percent higher than that reported during the same period in 2015 (n=87 411).

Singapore
In week 44, there were 86 dengue cases reported in Singapore. The cumulative number of cases in 2016 (12 525) is 42.5 percent higher than that reported during the same period of 2015 (8786) due to a large number of cases in early 2016. However, the number of cases is decreasing after week 36, and the number of cases in week 44 was the 2nd lowest in the past 6 years.

Cambodia (No updates)
From 1 Jan to 17 May 2016, there have been 1771 cases of dengue and 4 deaths reported in Cambodia. In May 2016, there were 168 cases and no deaths reported. The number of cases remains low and stable at this point.

Lao PDR (no update)
As of 28 Oct 2016, there were 4658 cases of dengue with 10 deaths reported in Lao PDR in 2016. From 22 to 28 Oct 2016, 185 new dengue cases and no deaths were reported. The number of cases is higher than the same period in 2014-2015.

Viet Nam (No update)
As of 31 Aug 2016, there were 63 504 cases of dengue including 20 deaths reported in 44 out of 63 provinces in Viet Nam. In August 2016, there were 16 547 cases reported, including 4 deaths. The cumulative number of cases increased by 97 percent with a decrease of 3 deaths compared to the same period in 2015. Compared to the median in 2011-2015 period, the cumulative number of dengue cases has increased by 99.7 percent.

Southern Hemisphere
---------------
Australia
As of 31 Oct 2016, there were 1930 laboratory-confirmed dengue cases in Australia. The number of cases reported has been decreasing since March 2016, and it follows the seasonal trends (2011-2015).

Pacific Islands Countries and Areas
---------
French Polynesia (No update)
In week 42, 22 confirmed dengue cases were reported in French Polynesia. Four (18 percent) of the 22 cases were confirmed as DENV-1 infection.

Papua New Guinea
From 1 Jan to 6 Nov 2016, 80 imported cases of dengue with travel history to Papua New Guinea were reported by Queensland Health (Weekly Report on overseas acquired dengue notifications). Among these cases, 5 were DENV-1, 57 were DENV-2, 4 were DENV-3, 3 were DENV-4 and 11 cases were of undetermined serotype.

New Caledonia
In October 2016, 19 dengue cases were reported, and the number of cases has been decreasing since June 2016.

